00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:35,760
And so now, we were in the middle of my list of Melville's understanding of what kind of meaning we can find in a godless world, where I mean godless with a capital G, that is, a world with no supreme being and a world with no onto theology, that is, because Buddhism doesn't have a supreme being, but it still has one total view about the true nature of everything.

2
00:00:35,760 --> 00:01:00,800
And once you give up on that, and it becomes more and more implausible to the people in our culture, and probably gradually the West takes over everything, and science takes over everything, and it becomes more and more implausible in all cultures, then what have you got left as possible sources of meaning?

3
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:10,961
And the only one I did last time talked about was the pagan, which is represented by KweQ.

4
00:01:11,281 --> 00:01:20,160
And that's got to do with some kind of saving understanding in the culture.

5
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:30,361
And part of that saving understanding, I don't, it isn't spelled out enough to be able to say just exactly how this works, is carved on Kwiquweg's body.

6
00:01:30,681 --> 00:01:58,281
That is, there's a tradition, and that tradition is sacred because, to put it in a Pascali way, I think I may have said this, custom is our nature, so that we are the kind of human beings that the tradition in our culture makes us, and things show up for us as the kind of things they are because of this tradition in our culture.

7
00:01:58,281 --> 00:02:03,160
So, in a way, the tradition is doing the job of the Creator God.

8
00:02:03,160 --> 00:02:11,560
It's making us, it sort of creates us and the things we deal with, and that's why it's sacred.

9
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:21,160
And just preserving it is some way preserving the saving power of that tradition.

10
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:27,001
And to preserve it, you don't have to do much because it's carved into your body anyway.

11
00:02:27,321 --> 00:02:38,040
But you do seem to have to have a sense of its importance, and that's why it gets carved on his body explicitly and why he copies it onto his coffin.

12
00:02:38,040 --> 00:02:53,321
The nearest thing I can think of it is Judaism, where there is a supreme being, but the supreme being, the creator God, doesn't seem to be nearly as important as the tradition, which is what is sacred and what you've got to keep.

13
00:02:53,320 --> 00:02:58,920
And the pagan is just that same idea, but without the supreme being.

14
00:02:58,920 --> 00:03:01,401
Okay, I don't have more to say about that.

15
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:03,321
I do have one more thing to say.

16
