00:04:32,321 --> 00:04:38,800
Did I give the impression that even dying Queque was still somehow sick?

32
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:39,761
It's not true.

33
00:04:39,761 --> 00:04:44,160
He's physically sick, but he's got immortal health in him.

34
00:04:44,160 --> 00:04:52,480
That's to say, his way of relating to the sacred in the tradition, in his culture, has healed him.

35
00:04:52,480 --> 00:05:08,761
And it was easier in his culture because it wasn't corrupted by onto-theology, so that people wanted something more, namely total experience of total God that made everything intelligible and gave you eternal fulfillment.

36
00:05:08,761 --> 00:05:16,120
When that gets in the way, as it does in Dante, everything, as we saw, else gets lost.

37
00:05:16,121 --> 00:05:25,081
So Quiqua didn't have to worry about that, and therefore his sacred tradition, as appreciated and carved in his body, healed him.

38
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:35,321
