00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:46,321
And then the sacred.

157
00:18:46,320 --> 00:18:55,761
In thoughts of the visions of the night, I saw long rows of angels in paradise, each with his hands in a jar of spermacetti.

158
00:18:55,761 --> 00:19:11,160
I mean, instead of getting a total contemplation of God in paradise forever, you get the opportunity to have, in this case, this sort of sensuous, loving, friendly relation to other people around this job.

159
00:19:11,161 --> 00:19:14,600
So, okay, so that's what there is to say about that.

160
00:19:16,921 --> 00:19:27,640
That activity gathers together the people and the angels, and in Heidegger jargon, that is the mortals and the gods, and so forth.

161
00:19:27,640 --> 00:19:29,161
And it creates little worlds.

162
00:19:29,161 --> 00:19:33,880
That's certainly a world for a while around the squeezing of the sperm.

163
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:35,080
So much for that.

